'''Vändåtberget''' is a [[nature reserve]] in [[Sweden]] located 50 kilometres northwest of the town [[Örnsköldsvik]]. The reserve was established in 1989 and has an area of 3 km<sup>2</sup>.<ref name="LanY"/>

The old forest of Vändåt is a habitat for the highly [[endangered species|endangered]] [[beetle]] ''Pytho kolwensis'', in the genus [[Pytho (beetle)|Pytho]] and the family [[Pythidae]]. It is also a habitat for a [[longhorn beetle]], ''Nothorhina muricata''.<ref name="Eckerberg"/>

The meaning of the name “Vändåt” is not known.

[[File:Pythos kolwensis - sällsynt urskogsskalbagge.jpg|thumb|left|200px|''Pytho kolwensis'', a rarity that can be found in Vändåtberget.]]

